{
  "stem": "150.3",
  "chunk_idx": 16,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I think it would be extremely conceited of me to believe that, that I'm somehow been designated an instrument of divine will.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I really cannot believe that.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I wish I could.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "What I see in the future is, you might consider it an optimistic or you might consider the pessimist view, and it's the same view.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I think that if things continue to go as well for the Jews here in America, then within 100 years or so, there will not be any Jews in America.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We'll assimilate just like we have in Spain and in Italy and in Germany until something happened, and they started mistreating us, and this reminded us.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And a lot of people died in the process.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Now to say that the Jews cannot disappear--that there is a divine will saying that the Jews have survived for 3,000 years and therefore, they must survive for another 3,000 year-- is probably accurate, but it's not really historically true because there are 10 tribes that disappeared.",
      "word_count": 47
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Where the hell are they?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Only two tribes were left that we know of and maintain the Jewish tradition.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And also, the Jews who are alive today really, technically, racially are not really Jews, if you look at all the blonde-haired, blue-eyed Jews in Eastern Europe, and all the black Jews in Ethiopia, and all the Chinese-looking Jews in China, there was an awful lot of mixed blood going around.",
      "word_count": 51
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was an awful lot of marriages and then fooling around going around.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Otherwise, we would all look like the Arabs.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I don't think it's in the race.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I don't think it's in the blood.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I think that, to a great extent, it is that the anti-Semites force us to remain Jewish.",
      "word_count": 17
    }
  ],
